Program: Discovery
Title: Ancient Olympics - the games
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryrb
Last Broadcast Date: 03 August 2004
Third in a series of programmes about the first Olympics. The Greeks divided their sports into two groups, 'heavy' and 'light', The heavy games included boxing, wrestling and a no-holds-barred grappling contest called pankration. The 'light' games were the running races. There were also equestrian events. Show less